column5: Formatting. I need to lose weight...

Merge pull request #13 from fay-jai/license

Update license with up-to-date year
Updated the package because npm said I have to.
Turned regexpbuilder into a module for npm.

Merge pull request #7 from nithesh/master

Fixes a typo in an example snippet on the README

Merge pull request #9 from LarryBattle/patch-1

Added definition of r
Fixes a typo in an example snippet on the README
Use typeof instead of being an idiot.

Ensure flags are not cleared when a subexpression is flushed.

Also ensure no duplicate flags.
Added globalMatch() and simplified flag-related code.

Bug fix: missing global flag in group numbering function

Added the global flag to the group numbering function as we want to
adjust all of the groups numbers, not just the first one we encounter.

Changed to lowercase naming convention.
At some point I became a Windows user and followed their stupid naming
conventions.

Improved code quality by getting rid of that stupid fucking
RegExpBuilder.prototype.methodName shit that Javascript likes because it
is fucking shit. Just have classical inheritance like every other
language motherfucker.
Now users can pass in \ to methods and it will be escaped.

Properly escaped digit(), tab(), whitespace() so they work (again).
Changed escaping method to regex for performance.

Attached functions to prototype instead of instance of object to save
memory when multiple RegExpBuilders are created. This means that the
functions are created once on the prototype, instead of created on every
new instance.
Moved non-javascript files out of this repository.

Renamed from_class() and not_from_class() to inside() and outside() as
they are shorter.
Changed semantics of anythingBut and somethingBut.

Increment the number of groups used if a passed in RegExpBuilder uses
groups and is to be combined with the existing RegExpBuilder.
Account for regular expressions with more than 9 groups.

Rename adjustGroupNumbering to incrementGroupNumbering. Remove internal
state reference from incrementGroupNumbering to make it easier to
refactor / debug, etc.

Forgot to rename one of the methods when adding the adjusted group
functionality.

When combining regular expressions, must adjust group numbering to make
sure the group references refer to the right groups.

Moved languages into their own folders.
Added anythingBut() and somethingBut().
Added Factory to shorten RegExpBuilder construction.

Python now has either() method that accepts mixed-type array of strings
/ RegExpBuilder objects instead of all of the either_string, or_string,
either_like, or_like methods.

either and or are now overloaded instead of having eitherLike and
orLike.

Renamed anything() to something().
Added anything(), any(), notWhitespace(), notDigit(), notDigits(),
notLetter(), notLetters().
Fixed python naming convention.
Made ahead() and notAhead() chainable. eg - ahead().ahead().ahead()

Renamed behind() and notBehind() to ahead() and notAhead(). Added
append() and optional().
Forgot to change min to exactly in whitespace method.

whitespace() now works for single or multiple whitespace depending on
the context, added new methods: digit(), digits(), letter(), letters(),
lowerCaseLetter(), lowerCaseLetters(), upperCaseLetter(),
upperCaseLetters().
Removed oneOrMore(), doesn't fit well into the API.

Added oneOrMore(), renamed start() and end() to startOfInput() and
endOfInput(), added startOfLine() and endOfLine().
Added maybeSome() method, fixed dart and python versions.

Methods now accept new RegExpBuilder objects instead of functions as a
it looks a bit cleaner in javascript.

Added new methods: anything(), lineBreak(), lineBreaks(), whitespace(),
tab(), tabs().
Removed unnecessary start() and end() from example in readme.

Renamed either to eitherLike, or to orLike, eitherString to either,
orString to or, behind to behindPattern, notBehind to notBehindPattern,
and added behind(string), and notBehind(string).

Renamed asCapturingGroup to asGroup.
Added ofGroup to reference group inside regular expression.
Forgot that I should be using StringBuilder in java, not StringBuffer.
Pedantic - changed order of method declarations.
Removed legacy method from python version.

Added eitherString("p").orString("q"), which translates to either((r) =>
r.exactly(1).of("p")).or((r) => r.exactly(1).of("q")). Also removed the
other StringBuffer from dart version.

Dart version now uses lists instead of string buffer due to performance
issues. All versions now support chained "or" sequence. Added unit test
for this new feature.

Dart version now supports chaining of "or", such as:

either().or().or().or()

No longer escapes the escape character as it then ignores special
characters and doesn't escape the escape character properly and so on.
Users will have to escape the escape character themselves.
Improved qualtiy of javascript test library.
Fixed python version. Added python unit tests.
Fixed 'or' bug in javascript version. Added javascript tests.
Fixed notBehind bug in java version. Added java unit tests.
Fixed notBehind bug. Added unit tests for dart version.

Added more privacy scope to dart version and added shortcut boolean
evaluation to python version.
Fixed end() bug and added privacy scope to some interal methods.

Changed requiring of Set to requiring of List in methods such as "from"
due to the fact that Sets aren't as well supported in Dart for various
methods.
Performance improvements = removed some object creation.

Added ignoreCase and multiLine flags. (new RegExpBuilder().ignoreCase =
true).
Changed Strings.join to Strings.concatAll as don't need separator.

Works with newer versions of Dart.
Improved performance of special character replacing.
Added capturing groups (asCapturingGroup())
